The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Bayelsa State has constituted a nine-member committee to reconcile aggrieved members of the party. According to the chairman of the party, Mr. Cleopas Moses, said in a statement that the reconciliation panel is coming on the heels of the recent primary election where Senator Douye Diri emerged as the candidate of the party for the November 16, 2019 governorship election in the state. Moses noted that there was a need to carry all members of the party along and ensure its unity ahead of the governorship election. Taraba crisis: CAN chairman predicts food crisis Dethroned Emir emerges PDP deputy chairman in Zamfara Dissolution: OYSIEC members drag Makinde to court Oyo guber: APC expresses dismay at tribunal’s ruling ALSO READ: 25th economic summit to focus exploding population ― Ahmed According to him, the committee will be chaired by Senator Inatimi Rufus-Spiff with a former Secretary to the State Government, Chief Gideon Ekeuwei, as secretary. Other members are Senator Emmanuel Diffa, Chief Bright Erewari-Igbeta, Hon. Darius Obiene, Chief George Okirien, Chief Israel Igbori, Hon. Solomon Agwanagha and Millionaire Asangba. The party chairman further urged members to remain steadfast and not listen to the propaganda and blackmail being spread by the opposition in the state. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
